%N A288247 2 * smallest possible area of a simple n-sided lattice polygon whose vertex coordinates x and y are both independent permutations of the integers 1 ... n, subject to the condition that none of its edges are mutually parallel.
%C A288247 It is conjectured that a(n) = n-2 for all n > 15, i.e. the bound of Pick's theorem is achievable for all larger n.
%C A288247 Results are partially based on the discussion in the newsgroup dxdy.ru, see link.
